Sequel to the verdict of the Appeal Court which favoured him, Osun State Governor, Mr Gboyega Oyetola has urged the people of Osun State to remain peaceful.  Whereas the candidate of the People’s Democratic Party, Senator Ademola Adeleke has declared that he was heading to the Supreme Court to seek redress on the decision of the Appeal Court.  In a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr Adeniyi Adesina, the governor said truth has prevailed over falsehood with his victory at the Appeal Court.  He urged all the residents of the to be peaceful and to go about their legitimate businesses.  According to him, “We give praise to Almighty God for today’s victory at the Court of Appeal sitting in Abuja. The victory has validated the mandate you freely gave to us on September 22 and 27, 2018.”  “You spoke with conviction; your voice and choice are clear to the world, and the judiciary, the last hope of the people and arbiter of the truth, has proved to the world that it is always on the side of justice.”  “After months of uncertainty and wait in judicial wilderness, truth has finally prevailed over falsehood and the voice of the majority has ultimately gained dominance over the phoney manipulation of an unscrupulous minority”  “This victory has proven to all and sundry that there is a limit to the extent falsehood and propaganda can thrive over truth and the will of the people.”   Only Oyo govt. can appeal Killer lawyer''s sentence — Prosecutor Female lawyer bags 7-yrs for stabbing husband to death Pastor to die for murdering wife Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin